{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RVYx4JG1ugKG2Y8vs9GYRY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The logs reveal the issue clearly:\n\n```\nW0625 18:49:19.368598      13 controller.go:349] ignoring ingress canary-stable in demo based on annotation : no object matching key \"nginx\" in local store\nI0625 18:49:19.377276      13 store.go:439] \"Ignoring ingress because of error while validating ingress class\" ingress=\"demo/canary-stable\" error=\"no object matching key \\\"nginx\\\" in local store\"\n```\n\nThe ingress class `nginx` doesn't exist in this cluster! The controller is `ingress-1` (which handles `ingress-1` class). \n\nThe stable and canary Ingresses reference `ingressClassName: nginx`, but looking at the logs, the controller is ignoring both the `ingress-2` and `nginx` IngressClasses because their spec.controller values don't match what this controller instance is watching for.\n\nLater logs show the controller is actually using `ingress-1` as its class, and `demo-app-alt` is configured with that class. But then there's an error where `demo/otel-echo` can't find the `nginx` class in the store at all. I need to look at what IngressClass resources actually exist and what controller each one is configured for.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3869,"cache_read_input_tokens":32536,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3869},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2912982a-534d-4c5e-8f7a-b7408e197d9e","uuid":"0fe568f8-387c-410a-8ad9-83d0998987fc","request_id":"req_011CcQUmDrKxQszTHCikoVjy"}
